Anyways, here&#39;s what I was trying to say when I goofed it up.<br>
<br>
1. You can use Time Lapse (Phrups effect) on a Climbing Staff being discarded from the hand in order to prevent it&#39;s effect from taking place. This ruling owned me b/c I was not aware of it until the situation came up.<br>
<br>
2. You can only Climbing Staff inhibitors when they are played. It was ruled previously that you could Staff an Entangle on your own turn, played on your opponents turn, in order to turn it off. Not so anymore.<br>
